# Blog Post Standards

Every post must include frontmatter with:

```yaml
---
title: "Post Title"
date: YYYY-MM-DD
description: "A clear 50-160 character summary for search and sharing."
categories:
  - Notes
tags:
  - blog
authors:
  - you
draft: false
---
```

## Content Rules

- Use one H1 matching the post title.
- Put `<!-- more -->` after the opening excerpt when the post is ready to publish.
- Keep headings direct and descriptive.
- Use descriptive links.
- Preserve the author's voice when editing drafts.

## Checks

- Run `npm run seo:check`.
- Run `npm run content-map:generate` after meaningful content changes.
- Run `npm run crosslink:suggest` before publishing.
